# Introduction {.unnumbered}

```{r, echo=FALSE,warning=FALSE,message=FALSE}
params<-list(
  version= '0.2',
  modules = c( 'Data, Plotting, Pre-processing, Statistics, Clustering, Dimensional reduction, Pathway analysis, Predictive modeling, Network analysis, Reporting'))


library(shiny)
library(dave.help)
mods<-parse_modules(params$modules) #
htmltools::tagList(rmarkdown::html_dependency_font_awesome()) # required for icons
```



`r module_title('DAVe: Data Analysis and Visualization engine')`

![](img/dave.main/full.png){.center}

##### DAVe, application interactively combines statistics, clustering, data exploration and visualization with machine learning, functional and network analysis to create information and context rich mapped networks. The following manual describes a selection of available workflows. Get ready to connect your data with context!

<br>

![](img/dave.main/nav.png){.center}

### Modules
##### DAVe is comprised of `r mods$length` modules covering: `r grammatical_paste(mods$modules) %>% tolower()` domains. Each module contains a `calculate`, `explore`, `plot` and `report` components.

### Actions
#### `r dcr_gr('Calculate')` 

<hr>
##### This tab is used to set the method options and view the results summary and tabular output.
![](img/dave.ml/model/results.png){.center}

#### `r dcr_gr('Explore')` 

<hr>

##### Interactively explore the results.
![](img/dave.main/explore.png){.center}

#### `r dcr_gr('Plot')`

<hr>
##### View and tune your data visualizations.
![](img/dave.main/plot.png){.center}

#### `r dcr_gr('Report')`

<hr>

##### Create data analysis summaries and reproducible reports.
